cs.MA, cs.DC, cs.SE, cs.AI, cs.DS

Reasoning: 
- cs.MA (Multiagent Systems) is the most likely category as the paper proposes a model of agent-based Virtual Organisations (VOs) and characterizes agents by their goals and roles within VOs. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is also likely as the paper discusses service grids and their associated operational model for the creation of VOs. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is a possible category as the paper abstracts away from any realisation choices of the service grid application and focuses on the workflow of services and corresponding contracts suitable for achieving the goals of the participating agents. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper deals with agents and their interactions within VOs. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a less likely category as the paper does not focus on data structures or algorithms, but rather on the conceptual framework for VOs as agent societies.
